===Proper noun===
'''Frisco'''
# [[San Francisco]], [[California]]
#:''Left my home in Georgia, headed for the Frisco Bay, I had nothin' to live for, looks like nothin's gonna come my way, I'm just sittin' on the dock of the bay, watchin' the tide roll away, sittin' on the dock of the bay, wastin' time.'' - [[w:(Sittin' on) the Dock of the Bay|(Sittin' on) the Dock of the Bay]], [[w:Otis Redding|Otis Redding]]

===Usage note===
San Francisco's [[w:Joshua A. Norton|Emperor Norton]] proposed a twenty-five dollar fine for those using this word:
:Whoever after due and proper warning shall be heard to utter the abominable word "Frisco," which has no linguistic or other warrant, shall be deemed guilty of a High Misdemeanor, and shall pay into the Imperial Treasury as penalty the sum of twenty-five dollars.
Many modern-day San Franciscans would be inclined to agree.